 "cells": [
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4,\n",
    " \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\n",
    "  \"kernelspec\": {\n",
    "   \"display_name\": \"Python 3\",\n",
    "   \"language\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python3\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  \"language_info\": {\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"version\": \"3.11.0\"\n",
    "  }\n",
    " },\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Hate Speech Classification\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**NLP Project 8 of 100 · Beginner Text Classification**\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook builds a **multi-class classifier** that detects hate speech, offensive language, and neutral content. We use the hate_speech_offensive dataset and compare TF-IDF baselines against ModernBERT.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Models:** TF-IDF + MultinomialNB, LogReg, LinearSVC, SGD, RF, ModernBERT\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Metrics:** Accuracy, Macro-F1, Per-class Precision/Recall, Confusion Matrix\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Distinguish hate speech from offensive-but-not-hateful language\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Handle 3-class imbalanced text classification\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Compare TF-IDF and transformer approaches\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Discuss ethical challenges in hate speech detection\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Problem Statement\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Given a social media post, classify it as: **hate speech**, **offensive language**, or **neither**. This is a 3-class problem where the distinction between hate speech and offensive language is nuanced.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Project Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Hate speech causes real harm; automated detection helps platforms respond faster.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Distinguishing hate speech from offensive language prevents over-censoring.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Property | Value |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"|----------|-------|\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Source | HuggingFace `hate_speech_offensive` |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Classes | 3 (hate_speech, offensive, neither) |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Records | ~25,000 tweets |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Language | English |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Davidson et al. (2017) hate speech dataset. Academic use.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Environment Setup\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in ['pandas','numpy','matplotlib','seaborn','scikit-learn','datasets','transformers','accelerate']:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try: importlib.import_module(pkg.replace('-','_'))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,'-m','pip','install','-q',pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('Ready.')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Imports\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import os,json,warnings,random\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np, pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression,SGDClassifier\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.calibration import CalibratedClassifierCV\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score,f1_score,classification_report,confusion_matrix\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print('Imports loaded.')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Configuration / Constants\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED=42; TFIDF_MAX=15000; LABEL_NAMES=['hate_speech','offensive','neither']\\n\",\n",
    "    \"MODEL_NAME='answerdotai/ModernBERT-base'; MAX_LEN=128; BS=16; EPOCHS=3; LR=2e-5\\n\",\n",
    "    \"random.seed(SEED); np.random.seed(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SAVE_DIR=os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath('__file__'))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Seed: {SEED}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Dataset Download or Loading\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"from datasets import load_dataset\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ds = load_dataset('hate_speech_offensive', split='train')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = ds.to_pandas()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Dataset: {df.shape}, Columns: {list(df.columns)}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Dataset has 'tweet', 'class' (0=hate_speech, 1=offensive, 2=neither)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"text_col = 'tweet' if 'tweet' in df.columns else df.columns[0]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"label_col = 'class' if 'class' in df.columns else df.columns[-1]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = df.rename(columns={text_col: 'text', label_col: 'label'})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = df[['text','label']].dropna().reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df['label_name'] = df['label'].map({0:'hate_speech',1:'offensive',2:'neither'})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Label distribution:\\\\n{df[\\\"label_name\\\"].value_counts()}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Data Validation Checks\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f'Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Duplicates: {df.duplicated(subset=[\\\"text\\\"]).sum()}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = df.drop_duplicates(subset=['text']).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = df[df['text'].str.strip().ne('')].reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Final: {len(df)} rows')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"df['text_len']=df['text'].str.len()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(14,5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for lbl in [0,1,2]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    s=df[df['label']==lbl]; axes[0].hist(s['text_len'],bins=40,alpha=0.5,label=LABEL_NAMES[lbl])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title('Text Length'); axes[0].legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df['label_name'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar',ax=axes[1],color=['red','orange','steelblue'],edgecolor='black')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title('Class Distribution')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR,'eda_distributions.png'),dpi=100); plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Heavily imbalanced: ~77% offensive, ~17% neither, ~6% hate_speech. Macro-F1 is essential.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(f'Class proportions:\\\\n{(df[\\\"label_name\\\"].value_counts(normalize=True)*100).round(1)}')\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Train/Validation/Test Split Strategy\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"X=df['text'].values; y=df['label'].values\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X_train,X_test,y_train,y_test=train_test_split(X,y,test_size=0.2,random_state=SEED,stratify=y)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Train: {len(X_train)}, Test: {len(X_test)}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"TF-IDF on raw tweets. `class_weight='balanced'` essential for minority hate_speech class.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Feature Engineering\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"tfidf=TfidfVectorizer(max_features=TFIDF_MAX,sublinear_tf=True,ngram_range=(1,2),min_df=2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X_tr=tfidf.fit_transform(X_train); X_te=tfidf.transform(X_test)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'TF-IDF: {X_tr.shape}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Baseline Model: TF-IDF + MultinomialNB\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"bl=MultinomialNB(alpha=0.5); bl.fit(X_tr,y_train)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"yp=bl.predict(X_te)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Baseline Macro-F1: {f1_score(y_test,yp,average=\\\"macro\\\"):.4f}')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(classification_report(y_test,yp,target_names=LABEL_NAMES))\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Traditional ML Classifier Comparison\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> LazyPredict/FLAML not used for NLP.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"clfs={'MultinomialNB':MultinomialNB(alpha=0.5),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"      'LogReg':LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000,random_state=SEED,class_weight='balanced'),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"      'LinearSVC':CalibratedClassifierCV(LinearSVC(max_iter=2000,random_state=SEED,class_weight='balanced'),cv=3),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"      'SGD':CalibratedClassifierCV(SGDClassifier(loss='hinge',random_state=SEED,class_weight='balanced',max_iter=1000),cv=3),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"      'RF':RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200,random_state=SEED,class_weight='balanced',n_jobs=-1)}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"results=[]; trained_models={}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for name,clf in clfs.items():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    clf.fit(X_tr,y_train); yp=clf.predict(X_te)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    r={'Model':name,'Accuracy':accuracy_score(y_test,yp),'Macro_F1':f1_score(y_test,yp,average='macro')}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    results.append(r); trained_models[name]=(clf,yp)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"{name:15s} | Acc={r['Accuracy']:.4f} | Macro-F1={r['Macro_F1']:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pd.DataFrame(results).sort_values('Macro_F1',ascending=False)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Why FLAML Is Not Used Here\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> Not applicable for NLP.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"## Transformer Approach: ModernBERT Fine-Tuning\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"tr_res=None; y_pred_t=None\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    import torch\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    from transformers import AutoTokenizer,AutoModelForSequenceClassification,Trainer,TrainingArguments\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    from datasets import Dataset\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    dev='cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu'; torch.manual_seed(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    td=pd.DataFrame({'text':X_train,'label':y_train})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if len(td)>8000: td=td.sample(n=8000,random_state=SEED).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tds=Dataset.from_pandas(td); eds=Dataset.from_pandas(pd.DataFrame({'text':X_test,'label':y_test}))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tok=AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    def tf(ex): return tok(ex['text'],truncation=True,padding='max_length',max_length=MAX_LEN)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tds=tds.map(tf,batched=True); eds=eds.map(tf,batched=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tds.set_format('torch',columns=['input_ids','attention_mask','label'])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    eds.set_format('torch',columns=['input_ids','attention_mask','label'])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    m=AutoModelForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME,num_labels=3).to(dev)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    a=TrainingArguments(output_dir='./out',num_train_epochs=EPOCHS,per_device_train_batch_size=BS,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        per_device_eval_batch_size=BS*2,warmup_ratio=0.1,weight_decay=0.01,learning_rate=LR,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        eval_strategy='epoch',save_strategy='no',logging_steps=50,report_to='none',seed=SEED,fp16=torch.cuda.is_available())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    def cm(ep): p=np.argmax(ep.predictions,axis=1); return {'accuracy':accuracy_score(ep.label_ids,p),'macro_f1':f1_score(ep.label_ids,p,average='macro')}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    t=Trainer(model=m,args=a,train_dataset=tds,eval_dataset=eds,compute_metrics=cm)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    t.train(); po=t.predict(eds); y_pred_t=np.argmax(po.predictions,axis=1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tr_res={'Model':'ModernBERT','Accuracy':accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred_t),'Macro_F1':f1_score(y_test,y_pred_t,average='macro')}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"ModernBERT Macro-F1={tr_res['Macro_F1']:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    del m,t; torch.cuda.empty_cache() if torch.cuda.is_available() else None\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e: print(f'Transformer skipped: {e}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Top 3 Model Selection\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"ar=results.copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if tr_res: ar.append(tr_res)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"adf=pd.DataFrame(ar).sort_values('Macro_F1',ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(adf.to_string(index=False,float_format='{:.4f}'.format))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"top3=adf.head(3)['Model'].tolist(); print(f'Top 3: {top3}')\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"t3d={}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for n in top3:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if n in trained_models: t3d[n]=trained_models[n][1]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    elif n=='ModernBERT' and y_pred_t is not None: t3d[n]=y_pred_t\\n\",\n",
    "    \"nc=len(t3d)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,nc,figsize=(6*nc,5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if nc==1: axes=[axes]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i,(n,yp) in enumerate(t3d.items()):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(y_test,yp),annot=True,fmt='d',cmap='Blues',\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                xticklabels=LABEL_NAMES,yticklabels=LABEL_NAMES,ax=axes[i])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    axes[i].set_title(n)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR,'confusion_matrices.png'),dpi=100); plt.show()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for n,yp in t3d.items(): print(f'\\\\n{n}'); print(classification_report(y_test,yp,target_names=LABEL_NAMES))\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## Error Analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"bp=t3d[top3[0]]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"edf=pd.DataFrame({'text':X_test,'true':y_test,'pred':bp})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"errs=edf[edf['true']!=edf['pred']]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f'Errors: {len(errs)}/{len(edf)} ({len(errs)/len(edf)*100:.1f}%)')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"edf['true_n']=edf['true'].map(lambda x:LABEL_NAMES[x]); edf['pred_n']=edf['pred'].map(lambda x:LABEL_NAMES[x])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"cp=edf[edf['true']!=edf['pred']].groupby(['true_n','pred_n']).size().sort_values(ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(cp.head(5))\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Hate speech vs offensive language is inherently ambiguous — even human annotators disagree.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. The offensive class dominates (~77%), making hate speech detection harder.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Context matters: identical words can be hateful or casual depending on who/how they're used.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. ModernBERT handles subtle context better than TF-IDF.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. 3-class scheme oversimplifies. 2. Twitter-specific language. 3. Annotator bias. 4. English only.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## How to Improve\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Add context (conversation thread). 2. Use demographics-aware evaluation. 3. Add severity scores.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Production Considerations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Real-time moderation needs <100ms latency. Escalation queues for uncertain predictions.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Treating hate speech and offensive language as the same. 2. Using accuracy on imbalanced data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Merge hate_speech+offensive into binary (harmful vs not). Compare results.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Hate speech detection is a nuanced 3-class NLP problem.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. TF-IDF + balanced LogReg is a competitive baseline.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. ModernBERT helps with context-dependent ambiguity.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Use macro-F1 for fair evaluation across imbalanced classes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
